quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  61,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies God. For He ˹alone˺ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  61,2,O believers! Why do you say what you do not do
  61,3,How despicable it is in the sight of God that you say what you do not do
  61,4,Surely God loves those who fight in His cause in ˹solid˺ ranks as if they were one concrete structure
  61,5,"˹Remember, O Prophet,˺ when Moses said to his people, “O my people! Why do you hurt me when you already know I am God’s messenger to you?” So when they ˹persistently˺ deviated, God caused their hearts to deviate. For God does not guide the rebellious people"
  61,6,"And ˹remember˺ when Jesus, son of Mary, said, “O children of Israel! I am truly God’s messenger to you, confirming the Torah which came before me, and giving good news of a messenger after me whose name will be Aḥmad.” Yet when the Prophet came to them with clear proofs, they said, “This is pure magic.”"
  61,7,Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies about God when invited to submit ˹to Him˺? For God does not guide the wrongdoing people
  61,8,"They wish to extinguish God’s light with their mouths, but God will ˹certainly˺ perfect His light, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  61,9,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ˹true˺ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others, even to the dismay of the polytheists"